<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,295,321]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after late Dr. C. Siddappaji, a very talented field entomologist and was instrumental in exploring leafhopper fauna in Mudigere area of 
<collectingRegion box="[844,963,331,357]" country="India" name="Karnataka" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Karnataka</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="75" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,367,393]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species externally resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1918" box="[699,945,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Gunghuyana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cingalensis">
<emphasis box="[699,858,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">G. cingalensis</emphasis>
Distant
</taxonomicName>
but differs in being smaller in size. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Viraktamath &amp; Yeshwanth, 2020" authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Yeshwanth" authorityYear="2020" box="[214,395,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Advikus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andamanicus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[214,395,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">A. andamanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[404,495,403,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[404,495,403,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Viraktamath &amp; Yeshwanth, 2020" authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Yeshwanth" authorityYear="2020" box="[552,734,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Advikus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radhamaniae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[552,734,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">A. radhamaniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[742,833,403,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[742,833,403,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in lacking a dark brown spot ventrad of the pronotal lateral carinae and in the presence of reddish brown posterior submarginal patches on the pronotum in the male. However, the three species have entirely different male genitalia.
</paragraph>
